1105
00:40:39,737 --> 00:40:42,440
and three of Daphne's brothers
just ran off into the woods.

1106
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:43,808
(knocking)

1107
00:40:43,808 --> 00:40:45,309
Ah.

1108
00:40:46,710 --> 00:40:48,679
Hello.
Here's your wine, sir.

1109
00:40:48,679 --> 00:40:50,681
Yes. Thank you very
much, young man.

1110
00:40:50,681 --> 00:40:52,950
Uh, and, uh,
this is for you.

1111
00:40:52,950 --> 00:40:53,818
What is this?

1112
00:40:53,818 --> 00:40:55,719
Well, Niles,
I got to thinking

1113
00:40:55,719 --> 00:40:58,155
about our old friend Morrie

1114
00:40:58,155 --> 00:41:01,659
and how he kept this bottle
of wine his entire life

1115
00:41:01,659 --> 00:41:04,161
waiting for a special occasion.

1116
00:41:04,161 --> 00:41:05,663
And then, I thought

1117
00:41:05,663 --> 00:41:07,531
what occasion
am I saving it for?

1118
00:41:07,531 --> 00:41:09,867
And then I thought
about what a courageous thing

1119
00:41:09,867 --> 00:41:10,868
you did last night--

1120
00:41:10,868 --> 00:41:14,205
taking that chance.

1121
00:41:14,205 --> 00:41:16,373
And that's worth a toast.

1122
00:41:16,373 --> 00:41:17,241
No, no, Frasier...

1123
00:41:17,241 --> 00:41:18,509
Niles,
it's too late.

1124
00:41:18,509 --> 00:41:19,777
The foil is pierced.

1125
00:41:19,777 --> 00:41:21,779
I know this thing
between you and Mel

1126
00:41:21,779 --> 00:41:24,281
seems kind of bad
right now, but...

1127
00:41:24,281 --> 00:41:26,150
Oh, now, Dad, why
do you say that?

1128
00:41:26,150 --> 00:41:28,018
Just because I spent
the third night of my marriage

1129
00:41:28,018 --> 00:41:30,521
proposing to another woman?

1130
00:41:30,521 --> 00:41:31,989
Well, I'm just saying

1131
00:41:31,989 --> 00:41:33,491
that marriages survive
all kinds of stuff.

1132
00:41:33,491 --> 00:41:35,493
You know, you
might still be happy.

1133
00:41:35,493 --> 00:41:38,295
Ten years from now, this
could all be ancient history.

1134
00:41:38,295 --> 00:41:40,397
I hope you're right.

1135
00:41:40,397 --> 00:41:42,132
FRASIER:
All right, gentlemen.

1136
00:41:42,132 --> 00:41:44,535
Here we are.

1137
00:41:44,535 --> 00:41:48,038
Dad, Niles-- allow me.

1138
00:41:48,539 --> 00:41:50,808
To better days.

1139
00:42:05,689 --> 00:42:07,758
Dad, where did Morrie keep this?

1140
00:42:07,758 --> 00:42:08,993
In his wine rack.

1141
00:42:08,993 --> 00:42:10,027
Which is?

1142
00:42:10,027 --> 00:42:11,529
In the boiler room.
Oh, Lord.

1143
00:42:11,529 --> 00:42:14,532
I'll just save this little treat
for later.

1144
00:42:14,532 --> 00:42:17,001
Yes, well, thanks
for the thought.

1145
00:42:17,001 --> 00:42:19,436
You two should be running along.
I'll be fine.

1146
00:42:19,436 --> 00:42:21,205
All right, well,
take care, Niles.

